<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - LUBRICATING OIL PUMP, OIL FILTERS AND COOLER - LUBRICATING OIL
        PUMP - INSPECTION AND REPAIR
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="3">
        <title>INSPECTION AND REPAIR</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title></title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Visually inspect the rotors, housing and plate for nicks, burrs or scoring.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace any damaged components.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The inner and outer rotors are a matched set and cannot be replaced separately.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Inspect for Wear</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the radial clearance between the outer rotor and the pump housing using a feeler
                    gauge as shown in
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150917">9.17</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    . Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="e415_HL4150901.xml" xrefid="hl4150901">"SPECIFICATIONS"</hotlnk>. If radial
                    clearance exceeds the specifications, check housing to rotor clearance (see step 4).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check housing to rotor clearance as follows:</para>
            </step1>
            <para>
                <emph type="underscr">Method One</emph>
                <emph type="bold"></emph>
            </para>
            <para>Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150918">9.18</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the O-Ring removed from the oil pump housing, place a straightedge across the
                    housing.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4150916" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12273" filename="../figcg1/cg12273.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9.16. Remove Oil Pump Plate and Ring.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150917" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12274" filename="../figcg1/cg12274.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9.17. Check Outer Rotor to Housing Clearance.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150918" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12275" filename="../figcg1/cg12275.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9.18. Check Housing to Rotor Clearance (Method One).</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert an appropriate feeler gauge under the straightedge at the housing and outer
                    rotors. (See
                    <hotlnk document="e415_HL4150901.xml" xrefid="hl4150901">"SPECIFICATIONS"</hotlnk>.)
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If not within specifications, check the inner housing and rotors for wear. Replace worn
                    components, as required.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>
                <emph type="underscr">Method Two</emph>
                <emph type="bold"></emph>
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Refer to Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e415_194.xml" xrefid="ef4150919">9.19</hotlnk>.
                </emph>
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>An alternate method of measuring the housing to rotor clearance is the use of Plastigage(r)
                        just before assembling the oil pump to the front cover.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place a strip of Plastigage(r) onto the rotors (side facing out from engine).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new O-Ring in the oil pump housing and install the housing to the front
                    cover.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the housing and measure the Plastigage(r). (See
                    <hotlnk document="e415_HL4150901.xml" xrefid="hl4150901">"SPECIFICATIONS"</hotlnk>.)
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If not within specifications, check the rotors and inner housing for wear. Replace worn
                    components, if necessary.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If components are to be reused, clean the Plastigage(r) from the rotors or housing.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The Plastigage(r) may stick to either the rotors or the oil pump housing.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
